        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is previously healthy with no known chronic medical conditions and no prior hospitalizations, based on the available history. She is a kindergarten-aged child living with her family in the Czech Republic and has frequent exposure to other children, which is relevant because children commonly get more colds each year than adults and the illness spreads easily by close contact [MEDLINEPLUS:J00]. The current illness started recently with sore throat, headache, cough, and nasal congestion, followed by a low-grade fever today [MEDLINEPLUS:J00, SNOMED:J00, MEDDIALOG:J00:7].\n\nHer parent has been encouraging rest and fluids at home, which is appropriate supportive care for a common cold [MEDLINEPLUS:J00]. There is no evidence provided of asthma, recurrent ear infections, prior surgery, medication use, or drug allergies, so these are not reported."
          }
        ]
